The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 3i Infotech revenue up 26%

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT 

 Mumbai, April 23: 3i Infotech Limited, the newest entrant in stock exchanges, has posted a 26 per cent revenue growth for the year ended March 31.

 Revenues grew to Rs 292 crore from Rs 232 crore in the previous year, with gross margins jumping from 38 per cent to 43 per cent. Profit before interest, depreciation and taxation (PBDIT) leaped 200 per cent to Rs 50.87 crore.

 The board also recommended a full and final dividend of Re 1 per share. The 3i share closed at Rs 97.80 on Friday. The company has posted a consolidated profit after tax of Rs 32.11 crore for the last financial year. The EPS for the year has grown to Rs 6.88 as against a negative EPS in the previous year.

 Commenting on the improvement in operations, managing director and CEO V. Srinivasan said, ?The growth in revenues, gross and PBDIT margins is the result of the right strategies we have been following in increasing the software product mix in our revenues. 

 ?This has been achieved by penetrating newer markets through proper branding, marketing and sales strategies and making the products globally acceptable,? Srinivasan added. 

 While the company?s product strategy paid off, 3i Infotech reaped gains from its several cost cutting initiatives. Executive director Manoj Kunkalienkar said: ?The company, in addition to the sales penetration strategies, has substantially rationalised sales, general and administration expenses, thereby reducing it from 30 per cent of revenues in the previous year to 26 per cent in the last year.? 

 For the last quarter of the financial year, revenues grew to Rs 81.8 crore, registering a growth of 24 per cent over the corresponding quarter of the previous year and a growth of 8 per cent over the previous quarter. 




